&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working under the direct supervision of the Lead / Practice Nurse and strictly in accordance with specific practice guidelines and protocols, the Healthcare Assistant will assist the practice clinical team in the provision and delivery of prescribed programs of patient care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Oaklands Surgery and Yeovil Health Centre are looking for a Heath Care Assistant to join their team for 30 hours per week.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will ideally have experience of working in primary care although not essential, and be competent in basic healthcare duties. Candidates should possess excellent communication skills and an ability to organise their own time and workload.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An understanding, acceptance and adherence to the need for strict confidentiality is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please review the attached Job Description for more details on the role of an HCA at Oaklands Surgery and Yeovil Health Centre. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information about the role or if you have any questions then please call the Practice Manager Kathy Eke on 01935 473068 or email kathy.eke@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
